article.headline: Binghamton 85, Vermont 83
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- D.J. Rivera's layup with seven seconds left capped a Binghamton comeback from 17 points behind to defeat Vermont 85-83 Wednesday night. Emanuel Mayben scored 22 of his 31 points in the second half to lead the Bearcats (14-8, 7-3 America East) and Rivera finished with 21. Marqus Blakely had 18 points and Mike Trimboli 14 for Vermont (16-7, 7-3). The Catamounts led 74-57 with 7:10 left before the Bearcats went on a 22-4 run to take a 79-78 lead with 1:36 remaining. Trimboli tied the game at 83-83 on a 3-point play with 44 seconds left. Vermont held a 53-30 lead at the half and appeared to be cruising until Binghamton shot 62 percent in the second half. Emanuel finished with 11 of 17 from the field, including five of nine 3-pointers. Rivera added three more treys in four tries as the Bearcats hit 10 of 21.
